<paragraph id="IAS41_31" base="SL33624" principles="no"><paranum>31</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IAS 41"/><data name="paranum" value="31"/></prolog><body><p id="IAS41_P0185">The presumption in <xref id="IAS41_X0141" base="F1100564" href="IAS41_g30-33.dita#IAS41_g30-33/IAS41_g30-33_TI">paragraph 30</xref> can be rebutted only on initial recognition. An entity that has previously measured a <xref base="SL143220" href="IAS41_5.dita#IAS41_5/IAS41_P0108">biological asset<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0021"/></ph></xref> at its <xref base="SL143246" href="IAS41_8.dita#IAS41_8/IAS41_P0150">fair value<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0118"/></ph></xref> less <xref base="F6127376" href="IAS41_5.dita#IAS41_5/IAS41_P0110">costs to sell<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0059"/></ph></xref> continues to measure the biological asset at its fair value less costs to sell until disposal.</p></body></paragraph>